// InitiateOAuth2 - Initiate OAuth2 flow
// Endpoint used to initiate OAuth2 authorization flow. It redirects the user to the connection type's website for authorization, and afterwards redirects back to the provided `redirect_uri`, which must be whitelisted with Etleap (please contact Etleap support to whitelist a new redirect URI).
//
// Following successful authorization, the `redirect_uri` callback will include `code` and `state` query parameters.
//   - `code` can be used for OAuth2 connection creation, using generic [POST /connections](https://docs.etleap.com/docs/api-v2/b3A6NjUxODU4Ng-create-a-connection), or re-authorization using [PATCH /connections/{id}](https://docs.etleap.com/docs/api-v2/b3A6Mjc1MjA0ODk-update-a-connection). **Note:** code is short-lived and must be used immediately.
//   - `state` is a user-defined relay state, that is optional and will not be used by Etleap.
//
// If the authorization fails callback will include `state`, `error` and `error_description` query parameters, which will explain the reason for failure.
//
// Some connections require additional parameters for OAuth flow initiation. Please refer to the table below to check which query parameters are required for he specific connection. **Note:** query parameters for this endpoint are snake case as opposed to camel case in order to comply with OAuth2 conventions.
